<body>
    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Mutton Curry</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 kg mutton, cut into pieces</li>
            <li>2 large onions, finely chopped</li>
            <li>3 tomatoes, pureed</li>
            <li>1/2 cup yogurt</li>
            <li>1/4 cup cooking oil</li>
            <li>1/4 cup ghee</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon turmeric powder</li>
            <li>2 teaspoons red chili powder</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon garam masala</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon cumin powder</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon coriander powder</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon black pepper</li>
            <li>4-5 green cardamom pods</li>
            <li>4-5 cloves</li>
            <li>1 cinnamon stick</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
            <li>Fresh coriander leaves for garnish</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>meat</li>
            <li>indian</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Heat oil and ghee in a large pot. Add cardamom, cloves, and cinnamon stick and sauté until fragrant.</li>
            <li>Add chopped onions and cook until golden brown.</li>
            <li>Add ginger-garlic paste and sauté until the raw smell disappears.</li>
            <li>Add mutton pieces and brown them on all sides.</li>
            <li>Stir in turmeric powder, red chili powder, garam masala, cumin powder, coriander powder, black pepper, and salt. Mix well.</li>
            <li>Add pureed tomatoes and cook until the oil separates from the masala.</li>
            <li>Whisk yogurt and add it to the pot. Cook for another 5-7 minutes.</li>
            <li>Add enough water to cover the mutton. Cover the pot and simmer until the mutton is tender.</li>
            <li>Garnish with fresh coriander leaves.</li>
            <li>Serve hot with rice or naan.</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

